cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper deals with the application of deep learning for vessel detection in medical images, specifically fluorescein angiography (FA) images of the retina. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of human-in-the-loop learning, which falls under the category of interactive machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also mentions the use of unsupervised techniques for preliminary vessel detection, which falls under the category of unsupervised learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. The paper also discusses the use of geometric registration techniques, which falls under the category of image processing, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which is a subfield of multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible category.
